Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢The once was a hungry crow｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢Who wanted to get some feed｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢If only this beak were longer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢That feed would be a bit closer｣
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢A crow can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,｢can think... can think｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe, propose a hypothesis, experiment and then consider results.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn the way of scientific thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a ｢Thinking Observation｣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.00,0:01:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,An ant walking atop a notepad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.00,0:01:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try drawing a line across the ant's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.00,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears to dislike it but doesn't completely understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Again we block its path with a line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.00,0:02:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It avoids the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.00,0:02:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time we try to surround it with a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.00,0:02:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly it dislikes the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.00,0:02:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.00,0:02:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets out, and we surround it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As we expect it's isolated.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.00,0:02:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Observe for a short while.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.00,0:03:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It got out. Is it already used to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It walks across the lines in equanimity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try surrounding it with a new circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, it has become unable to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.00,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears it hasn't gotten used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today our problem deals with a magnet and some iron balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.00,0:05:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I bring it near the iron balls...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they stick together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.00,0:06:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But the iron balls themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.00,0:06:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of course don't stick together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Next we affix the magnet to the desk with some tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we place another magnet of the same type atop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If we bring an iron ball close, it sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, we place one more iron ball atop...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.00,0:06:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and this also sticks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen if we raise the topmost iron ball?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.00,0:07:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,1. Only the ball we're holding will be raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,2. The iron ball beneath will also be raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.00,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3. Furthermore, the magnet beneath will also be raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, what will happen?\NWe'll present the answer at the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, think really hard about this, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the answer from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, did you think carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:09:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's do it for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer it number 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.00,0:09:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The two iron balls together are raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Further more, if we try to raise the iron balls a bit further.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.00,0:09:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you suppose will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it fell. Let's try that once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.00,0:09:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw, it falls.\NWhy do you think that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When iron is brought near a magnet, instantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.00,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on we think for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.00,0:09:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From here everyone is a thinking crow.
